Text: Dragged out by Skel and Po, Cid ends up at Tuna King.

We've arrived! We've made it! We're part of the "it"
crowd!
Our ritz levels are off the chart!

The girls walking by can't help but check out our
super swag Mitsugucci outfits...
Pew! Pew! Hell yeah! Pew! Pew! Let's go!
A smooth transition from a reverse pick-up to a kiss is...
...pretty much guaranteed!
Smooooch!

(Mitsugucci... If it's design-related, maybe it's
something Eta came up with?)

(If not Gamma, Beta, or Epsilon... Nah, they all do
whatever they want.)
Hm?
Something's peeling off.
Wha—?
Aaaah! The Mitsugucci logo!
Without it, this outfit might as well be a knockoff!

Or, if I put it on another outfit, I could turn it
into a Mitsugucci...huh?
Tacky Max Clothing...
That's the logo of the store I bought it from!
Huh?! Is mine a fake too?!

Wait, on closer inspection, this logo doesn't look like
Mitsugoshi's either...
The real logo is more detailed!
That's why it's so cheap...
Mine's the same...
Hm?

(Come to think of it, Alpha and the others were the
ones who picked out my clothes.)

(I'm wearing a bunch of knockoffs from my previous
life...)

(I assumed it was the local fashion here since I've
spotted regular suits in the capital, but it looks
like Alpha and the gang had a hand in it.)

(They're using the knowledge from my previous life to
dominate the market. They'd be totally breaking
antitrust laws if there were any here.)

(They must've pissed off quite a few individuals
they've stolen profits from...)

(Individuals...they've...stolen profits from!
Stolen profits!)
But that ends today.
Cid?
You need to poop or something?
No.
I'm gonna go take back...everything.
What's up with him?
I mean, summer's almost over.
Cid heads back to his dorm room to start preparing.

Today is the long-awaited day that he meets with
Yukime.

He slips on a knockoff suit from Snow Fox Corporation,
which Yukime gave him as a present, and then adjusts
his tie.

Apparently, she manages a legitimate business
that operates outside the Lawless City. They're
currently in the middle of expanding their line
of Mitsugoshi knockoffs.

Even though Snow Fox is widely recognized as
the leading authority on plagiarizing its designs,
they've only been able to replicate a small
fraction of Mitsugoshi products.

He finishes the look by donning a white mask that
covers the area around his eyes.
Hehehe...
(Starting today, I'm a super elite agent.)
(Tonight, the world...)
(...will know my name!)
It is almost the time for the meeting.

Cid leaps out the window, and dashes off into
the night.
A while after the train departs, Yukime speaks.
Welcome...Mr. Shadow.
I've abandoned that name.

Ah, that's right. Now you're Mr. John Smith. It warms
my heart that you've decided to trust me.

There's profit in it for me. That's all there is to
it.

Oh my. A relationship built solely on profit? That's
far too sad, no?
You're no different, are you?
Aren't you the cold one.

Garter called a meeting of the MCA the other day.
They discussed tightening their grip on Mitsugoshi.
Mitsugoshi might fall faster than expected.
I see.

However, our plan remains the same. While Mitsugoshi
and the MCA crush each other...
...we take it all.

We'll need you to do some work to make this all
happen, Mr. Smith. Just be careful... That man is
behind the MCA.

The enigmatic swordsman who, seemingly out of
nowhere, rose above Garter and took control of
the MCA...
Gettan the Sword Devil.
I know him well.

A dangerous man who'll stop at nothing to achieve his
goals...
I swear...to deal with him myself...
I can hardly wait.

The battle for dominance in the capital's trade
business... In this conflict where money is paid
or in blood, who remains standing in the end...
Destroy it all, then start from scratch...
